00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:15.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.600 align:middle line:10%
>> This is "Book Tours,"
and I'm Corinne Edwards.

00:00:18.600 --> 00:00:21.150 align:middle line:10%
The world was fascinated
when the Dead Sea Scrolls

00:00:21.150 --> 00:00:24.010 align:middle line:10%
were discovered in 1946.

00:00:24.010 --> 00:00:25.860 align:middle line:90%
Now what do they tell us?

00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:28.040 align:middle line:90%
Are there hidden messages there?

00:00:28.040 --> 00:00:30.930 align:middle line:84%
Wisdom Television
welcomes Gregg Braden,

00:00:30.930 --> 00:00:33.510 align:middle line:90%
author of "The Isaiah Effect."

00:00:33.510 --> 00:00:38.020 align:middle line:84%
Greg turns to the Isaiah Scroll
as perhaps the most important

00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:41.130 align:middle line:84%
of the Dead Sea Scrolls
to offer insight

00:00:41.130 --> 00:00:43.920 align:middle line:84%
into a powerful form
of ancient prayer.

00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:46.290 align:middle line:84%
Welcome back to Wisdom
Television, Gregg.

00:00:46.290 --> 00:00:47.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, Corinne, it's a joy and
a pleasure to be here with you.

00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:47.970 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:00:47.970 --> 00:00:49.680 align:middle line:84%
>> It hasn't been that
long since you were here.

00:00:49.680 --> 00:00:50.480 align:middle line:90%
>> No, it hasn't.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:53.070 align:middle line:84%
And a lot has happened
since I was with you last.

00:00:53.070 --> 00:00:56.610 align:middle line:84%
>> You are a scholar of many
different ancient cultures

00:00:56.610 --> 00:00:59.940 align:middle line:84%
and ancient writings, but
there are people out there--

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:03.840 align:middle line:84%
there may be one or two people
out there who don't know what

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.700 align:middle line:84%
the Dead Sea Scrolls are,
and I'd like you to tell us.

00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:07.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, certainly.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:09.595 align:middle line:10%
And there are many
people that are just

00:01:09.595 --> 00:01:11.970 align:middle line:10%
beginning to understand the
breadth of what these scrolls

00:01:11.970 --> 00:01:12.960 align:middle line:10%
mean to us as well.

00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:15.600 align:middle line:84%
The Dead Sea Scrolls
are a library,

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:19.770 align:middle line:84%
an ancient library written by
a group of people we know today

00:01:19.770 --> 00:01:24.330 align:middle line:84%
as the Essenes, E-S-S-E-N-E-S.
We first hear of the Essenes

00:01:24.330 --> 00:01:27.085 align:middle line:84%
about 500 years before
the time of Christ.

00:01:27.085 --> 00:01:29.460 align:middle line:84%
These texts are important
because for the first time when

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:32.430 align:middle line:84%
they were discovered in
1946, in many instances

00:01:32.430 --> 00:01:35.760 align:middle line:84%
we saw some of the original
text that later became

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:38.310 align:middle line:84%
our Western biblical
texts in a form

00:01:38.310 --> 00:01:40.710 align:middle line:84%
that we had never
seen them before.

00:01:40.710 --> 00:01:43.200 align:middle line:84%
Much of the information
that we've always

00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:46.650 align:middle line:84%
relied upon in the West for
this kind of information

00:01:46.650 --> 00:01:49.080 align:middle line:84%
was edited in the
4th century AD.

00:01:49.080 --> 00:01:50.625 align:middle line:84%
And we've seen the
edited versions.

00:01:50.625 --> 00:01:52.500 align:middle line:84%
So it was with the
discovery of these scrolls

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:55.000 align:middle line:84%
in 1946, for the
first time we saw,

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.080 align:middle line:84%
for example, the original
book of the book Genesis.

00:01:58.080 --> 00:02:02.550 align:middle line:84%
We saw excerpts of texts that
were edited, the Book of Mary,

00:02:02.550 --> 00:02:04.470 align:middle line:84%
the gospel of the Book
of Mary, for example,

00:02:04.470 --> 00:02:05.700 align:middle line:90%
and the Book of Enoch--

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:09.570 align:middle line:84%
very key texts to help
us understand and flesh

00:02:09.570 --> 00:02:11.700 align:middle line:84%
out the framework
that we already

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:14.880 align:middle line:84%
have describing how we
relate to the cosmos and one

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:16.272 align:middle line:90%
another and the world around us.

00:02:16.272 --> 00:02:17.730 align:middle line:84%
>> How were they
discovered, Gregg?

00:02:17.730 --> 00:02:19.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's a
fascinating story, Corinne.

00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:22.375 align:middle line:84%
It's one of those innocent,
some people call, accidents.

00:02:22.375 --> 00:02:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, there
are no accidents.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:25.290 align:middle line:90%
It was a synchronicity.

00:02:25.290 --> 00:02:27.810 align:middle line:84%
A Bedouin shepherd boy
was throwing stones

00:02:27.810 --> 00:02:31.440 align:middle line:84%
into a cave, which apparently
he had done many times before.

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:33.510 align:middle line:90%
One day, a stone hit something.

00:02:33.510 --> 00:02:34.830 align:middle line:90%
It sounded different.

00:02:34.830 --> 00:02:37.470 align:middle line:84%
And upon investigation,
it was discovered

00:02:37.470 --> 00:02:40.170 align:middle line:84%
that that stone had
broken a vase that

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:43.210 align:middle line:84%
contained some of the
most complete scrolls

00:02:43.210 --> 00:02:47.220 align:middle line:84%
in what became Cave Number 1 of
the Dead Sea Scrolls library.

00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:51.650 align:middle line:84%
And between 1946 and 1959,
11 caves were discovered.

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:56.160 align:middle line:84%
25,000 fragments of
these texts comprising

00:02:56.160 --> 00:02:59.610 align:middle line:84%
about 800 the scrolls
were put together

00:02:59.610 --> 00:03:02.280 align:middle line:84%
from what was discovered
in these caves.

00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:05.310 align:middle line:84%
They were relegated to a
team of eight scholars,

00:03:05.310 --> 00:03:07.740 align:middle line:84%
and those eight scholars
had the responsibility

00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:09.930 align:middle line:84%
of piecing together
this information,

00:03:09.930 --> 00:03:12.880 align:middle line:84%
transcribing it, and compiling
in a way that's useful to us

00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:13.680 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:14.580 align:middle line:90%
>> How did it survive?

00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:16.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've been to
that area of the world.

00:03:16.220 --> 00:03:17.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:19.222 align:middle line:90%
>> It's so hot there.

00:03:19.222 --> 00:03:21.430 align:middle line:84%
Why did these-- the paper,
really, or the parchment--

00:03:21.430 --> 00:03:23.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, some-- the Scrolls--
it's such an amazing body

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:24.770 align:middle line:90%
of information.

00:03:24.770 --> 00:03:27.450 align:middle line:84%
Some of these scrolls
are on papyrus

00:03:27.450 --> 00:03:29.190 align:middle line:90%
like we find in Egypt today.

00:03:29.190 --> 00:03:31.650 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are on
animal hide, lamb skin.

00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:33.760 align:middle line:84%
Some of them were actually
written on copper.

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:34.560 align:middle line:90%
They're metallic.

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:36.490 align:middle line:84%
They're so brittle
that technologies

00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:38.610 align:middle line:84%
had to be developed
to even open them up.

00:03:38.610 --> 00:03:40.230 align:middle line:84%
They had to be sawed
into strips so we

00:03:40.230 --> 00:03:42.570 align:middle line:90%
could read what was in them.

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:44.820 align:middle line:84%
Many of them were
stored in the vases that

00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:47.010 align:middle line:84%
were sealed in with
resin and straw,

00:03:47.010 --> 00:03:50.260 align:middle line:84%
effectively sealing out
moisture for over 2,000 years.

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:51.060 align:middle line:90%
And this--

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:51.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm, amazing.

00:03:51.660 --> 00:03:52.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The interesting
thing, Corinne--

00:03:52.760 --> 00:03:55.020 align:middle line:84%
and many people believe these
are the oldest texts we have,

00:03:55.020 --> 00:03:56.020 align:middle line:90%
and that's not the case.

00:03:56.020 --> 00:03:58.560 align:middle line:84%
We have many texts
and traditions

00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:01.310 align:middle line:84%
that are much older than the
scrolls in Egypt, Babylonia,

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:04.922 align:middle line:84%
Sumeria, cuneiform
tablets, et cetera.

00:04:04.922 --> 00:04:06.630 align:middle line:84%
The reason these
scrolls are so important

00:04:06.630 --> 00:04:11.160 align:middle line:84%
is because they are the oldest
record that we have today

00:04:11.160 --> 00:04:14.160 align:middle line:84%
written in a language
that we still use today,

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:16.649 align:middle line:84%
in the Hebrew
language among some

00:04:16.649 --> 00:04:18.157 align:middle line:90%
of the others that were found.

00:04:18.157 --> 00:04:20.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's why these scrolls
are so important because we

00:04:20.490 --> 00:04:23.880 align:middle line:84%
know precisely what they're
saying rather than speculating

00:04:23.880 --> 00:04:26.640 align:middle line:84%
about what a temple wall
or a forgotten language

00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:28.560 align:middle line:90%
may perhaps be saying.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:32.400 align:middle line:84%
So the Aramaic language was
used as a form of Hebrew

00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:35.860 align:middle line:84%
as well, ancient biblical
Hebrew, as well as Greek.

00:04:35.860 --> 00:04:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Some of the scrolls
are in Greek today.

00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:38.990 align:middle line:84%
We're just beginning
to understand--

00:04:38.990 --> 00:04:39.900 align:middle line:90%
>> What do they say?

00:04:39.900 --> 00:04:41.983 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we're just beginning
to understand what--

00:04:41.983 --> 00:04:44.950 align:middle line:84%
when this information
was lost 1,700 years ago,

00:04:44.950 --> 00:04:48.210 align:middle line:84%
we began to lose
the understandings

00:04:48.210 --> 00:04:49.822 align:middle line:84%
of our relationship
to one another

00:04:49.822 --> 00:04:51.030 align:middle line:90%
in this Earth and the cosmos.

00:04:51.030 --> 00:04:55.290 align:middle line:84%
We began to feel very separate
from the world around us.

00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:57.000 align:middle line:84%
And in that
separateness, we have

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:58.920 align:middle line:84%
engineered this
marvelous technology

00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:00.177 align:middle line:90%
that serves us so well today.

00:05:00.177 --> 00:05:02.010 align:middle line:84%
We can have this taping,
and people see this

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:03.360 align:middle line:90%
all over the world.

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:05.850 align:middle line:84%
That's the result of a
path that has taken us

00:05:05.850 --> 00:05:07.560 align:middle line:90%
through our left brain--

00:05:07.560 --> 00:05:10.920 align:middle line:84%
very logical,
engineering-oriented

00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:13.620 align:middle line:90%
technologies which are valid.

00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:15.390 align:middle line:90%
However, they are incomplete.

00:05:15.390 --> 00:05:18.300 align:middle line:84%
And what we're finding is that
when these texts were edited,

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:22.080 align:middle line:84%
we lost another path that
is based in human feeling

00:05:22.080 --> 00:05:24.150 align:middle line:84%
and human emotion what
our own science now

00:05:24.150 --> 00:05:27.830 align:middle line:84%
is recognizing as an inner
technology of feeling

00:05:27.830 --> 00:05:28.630 align:middle line:90%
and emotion.

00:05:28.630 --> 00:05:30.780 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by
that is that when

00:05:30.780 --> 00:05:34.590 align:middle line:84%
we are able to elicit very
specific qualities of emotion

00:05:34.590 --> 00:05:37.620 align:middle line:84%
within our bodies,
it affects our bodies

00:05:37.620 --> 00:05:41.280 align:middle line:84%
in a predictable, repeatable
way, and now quantum science.

00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:43.710 align:middle line:84%
Our own modern 20th
century science

00:05:43.710 --> 00:05:46.740 align:middle line:84%
is finding that effect extends
to the world around us,

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:50.070 align:middle line:84%
and we can talk more about that
as we go through our interview.

00:05:50.070 --> 00:05:53.040 align:middle line:84%
>> You particularly-- you've
gone through all these Scrolls

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:55.590 align:middle line:84%
because you are a
scholar in this area,

00:05:55.590 --> 00:05:58.260 align:middle line:84%
but you particularly
picked the Isaiah Scrolls.

00:05:58.260 --> 00:05:59.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:59.280 --> 00:06:02.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Now when I went down to
look at the exhibit in Chicago

00:06:02.880 --> 00:06:06.810 align:middle line:84%
of the Dead Sea Scrolls, there
was very little, if anything--

00:06:06.810 --> 00:06:08.190 align:middle line:90%
>> I saw that exhibit as well.

00:06:08.190 --> 00:06:09.270 align:middle line:90%
>> --from the Isaiahs.

00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:12.150 align:middle line:84%
Why isn't anyone else
picking this up as something

00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:13.450 align:middle line:90%
more important than the others?

00:06:13.450 --> 00:06:15.180 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, it's very interesting.

00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:17.010 align:middle line:84%
The Isaiah text
was among the first

00:06:17.010 --> 00:06:18.810 align:middle line:84%
that were found in
the Cave Number 1,

00:06:18.810 --> 00:06:22.040 align:middle line:84%
the day that Bedouin boy
walked into that cave.

00:06:22.040 --> 00:06:25.860 align:middle line:84%
The Isaiah text is the
only complete manuscript

00:06:25.860 --> 00:06:28.200 align:middle line:84%
found in all of the
Dead Sea Scrolls,

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:31.290 align:middle line:84%
and it is on display today
in the Shrine of the Book

00:06:31.290 --> 00:06:32.850 align:middle line:90%
Museum in Jerusalem.

00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:36.840 align:middle line:84%
It is unrolled so that
we may read this text

00:06:36.840 --> 00:06:40.020 align:middle line:84%
and mount it on a
cylinder that is designed

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:44.100 align:middle line:84%
to retract into the
floor of this museum

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:47.370 align:middle line:84%
into a steel and
concrete-reinforced vault

00:06:47.370 --> 00:06:50.220 align:middle line:84%
with steel doors that
close over it to protect it

00:06:50.220 --> 00:06:51.600 align:middle line:84%
in the event of
a nuclear attack,

00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:54.315 align:middle line:84%
because it is believed
to be that precious.

00:06:54.315 --> 00:06:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And we have to ask ourselves,
what could possibly be

00:06:57.110 --> 00:07:00.660 align:middle line:84%
in a 2,500-year-old text
that would be so precious

00:07:00.660 --> 00:07:05.560 align:middle line:84%
that's designed in that way,
to be displayed in that way?

00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:08.130 align:middle line:84%
And that is why I
believe we're seeing

00:07:08.130 --> 00:07:10.800 align:middle line:84%
just the tip of the iceberg of
what Isaiah, the great prophet

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:13.380 align:middle line:84%
Isaiah, the first of the
Old Testament prophets

00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:14.545 align:middle line:90%
was saying to us.

00:07:14.545 --> 00:07:16.950 align:middle line:84%
And what we now know,
this information--

00:07:16.950 --> 00:07:19.800 align:middle line:84%
this was written before our
biblical texts were compiled

00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:21.000 align:middle line:90%
into what we see as a Bible.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.580 align:middle line:84%
This information
transcends, I believe,

00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:27.060 align:middle line:84%
many of the religions and
scientific and mystical

00:07:27.060 --> 00:07:28.020 align:middle line:90%
traditions.

00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:31.230 align:middle line:84%
It's the essence up around
which many of those traditions

00:07:31.230 --> 00:07:36.130 align:middle line:84%
were later built. And by
going to the earlier text,

00:07:36.130 --> 00:07:38.640 align:middle line:84%
we see in their completeness
and in their entirety

00:07:38.640 --> 00:07:43.050 align:middle line:84%
a message that was written and
left for all of humankind to--

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:46.512 align:middle line:84%
the opportunity to
transcend the suffering

00:07:46.512 --> 00:07:48.720 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps avert the greatest
tragedies ever to face

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:52.980 align:middle line:84%
humankind by evoking this
power that lives within us.

00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:54.180 align:middle line:90%
>> What do they say exactly?

00:07:54.180 --> 00:07:55.860 align:middle line:90%
What does this text say?

00:07:55.860 --> 00:07:58.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, in very eloquent
terms, the ancient Essenes,

00:07:58.650 --> 00:08:01.440 align:middle line:84%
they were poets as well as
scientists of their time.

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.150 align:middle line:84%
And the only words
they knew, Corinne--

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:04.830 align:middle line:84%
this is what's so
interesting, that they

00:08:04.830 --> 00:08:07.080 align:middle line:84%
were able to convey this in
the language of their time

00:08:07.080 --> 00:08:10.650 align:middle line:84%
and 2,500 years later we're
still making sense of it.

00:08:10.650 --> 00:08:13.360 align:middle line:84%
In the words of their time,
so eloquently they say this.

00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:15.480 align:middle line:84%
That the world
around us is simply

00:08:15.480 --> 00:08:19.770 align:middle line:84%
a mirror of what we
have become from within.

00:08:19.770 --> 00:08:25.080 align:middle line:84%
That the love, compassion, the
understanding and forgiveness

00:08:25.080 --> 00:08:27.450 align:middle line:84%
that we have become
within, we can fully

00:08:27.450 --> 00:08:29.670 align:middle line:84%
expect to see that mirrored
in the social conditions

00:08:29.670 --> 00:08:33.240 align:middle line:84%
around us, as well as the
condition of our bodies

00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:35.640 align:middle line:84%
and the anger and
the rage and the hate

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:38.708 align:middle line:84%
that we see in our
bodies, that we feel

00:08:38.708 --> 00:08:40.000 align:middle line:90%
in the presence of one another.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:41.820 align:middle line:84%
We can expect to
see that mirrored

00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:43.890 align:middle line:84%
in the social
conditions as well.

00:08:43.890 --> 00:08:45.750 align:middle line:84%
And then it takes
us one step further.

00:08:45.750 --> 00:08:50.790 align:middle line:84%
Isaiah-- in his language, in the
eloquent language of his day--

00:08:50.790 --> 00:08:52.290 align:middle line:90%
takes us one step further.

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:54.330 align:middle line:84%
And this is why I
chose the Isaiah text,

00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:57.030 align:middle line:84%
because he says, "Not only
are these things possible.

00:08:57.030 --> 00:09:00.480 align:middle line:84%
I will show you how to do these
things," through what we now

00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:05.550 align:middle line:84%
know is a modality of prayer
based in human feeling.

00:09:05.550 --> 00:09:07.980 align:middle line:84%
So prayer has no words,
no outer expression.

00:09:07.980 --> 00:09:10.560 align:middle line:90%
It was lost 1,700 years ago.

00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:13.350 align:middle line:84%
So to answer your question,
I chose the Isaiah text

00:09:13.350 --> 00:09:14.980 align:middle line:90%
because of its completeness.

00:09:14.980 --> 00:09:17.285 align:middle line:84%
What we've done in "The
Isaiah Effect," the book

00:09:17.285 --> 00:09:18.660 align:middle line:84%
"The Isaiah Effect,"
I could have

00:09:18.660 --> 00:09:22.840 align:middle line:84%
done in Buddhist traditions
or Islamic or Christian,

00:09:22.840 --> 00:09:24.390 align:middle line:84%
Jewish, Native
American traditions,

00:09:24.390 --> 00:09:27.450 align:middle line:84%
because elements
of this wisdom are

00:09:27.450 --> 00:09:29.857 align:middle line:84%
threads that weave
themselves throughout all

00:09:29.857 --> 00:09:30.690 align:middle line:90%
of these traditions.

00:09:30.690 --> 00:09:32.910 align:middle line:84%
However, in the
Isaiah text, I've

00:09:32.910 --> 00:09:35.430 align:middle line:84%
found them to be the most
complete, number 1, and, number

00:09:35.430 --> 00:09:38.070 align:middle line:84%
2, in a language that
we still use today.

00:09:38.070 --> 00:09:40.860 align:middle line:90%
And that is powerful for us.

00:09:40.860 --> 00:09:43.860 align:middle line:84%
>> When you were talking, it
came to my mind a quote from "A

00:09:43.860 --> 00:09:48.720 align:middle line:84%
Course in Miracles," which is
a spiritual channeled work.

00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:54.510 align:middle line:84%
And one of the quotes was,
"When you want only love,

00:09:54.510 --> 00:09:56.670 align:middle line:90%
you will see nothing else."

00:09:56.670 --> 00:09:58.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:04.980 align:middle line:10%
When we choose to become
the filters within that

00:10:04.980 --> 00:10:07.470 align:middle line:10%
mirror our heart's desire
and our greatest wishes,

00:10:07.470 --> 00:10:09.030 align:middle line:10%
it is through that
lens that we'll

00:10:09.030 --> 00:10:10.650 align:middle line:10%
see the events of
the world around us.

00:10:10.650 --> 00:10:13.400 align:middle line:84%
And I believe Isaiah
was saying this to us.

00:10:13.400 --> 00:10:15.480 align:middle line:84%
This all sounds very
nebulous and philosophical.

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:17.580 align:middle line:84%
And what's happened
is modern science now

00:10:17.580 --> 00:10:19.620 align:middle line:84%
is finding the
same relationships

00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:22.120 align:middle line:84%
that we can bear out under
laboratory conditions.

00:10:22.120 --> 00:10:22.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

